how to preserve a spider web and turn it into art. Here are the 5 simple steps: 

1.  find an abandoned spider web with no spider currently living in it 
2.  spray the web with white spray paint from about a foot away 
3.  take a piece of black paper and coat it with hair spray 
4.  gently push the wet side of the paper behind the web until it sticks 
5.  add a layer of spray-on glue to protect it and put it into a frame 

A fun way to observe and display nature’s beautiful creation! #natureart #diyprojects #easycrafts #spiderweb #diyart

Do you agree? 
Audio by John Cleese from a 1991 speech he gave on creativity. The full quote is worth a read:
“Nothing will stop you being creative so effectively as the fear of making a mistake. 
Creativity is not a talent. 
It is not a talent. 
It is a way of operating. 
An ability to play. 
To play is to experiment. 
What happens if I do this? 
What would happen if we do that? 
What if?
The very essence of playfulness is an openness to anything that may happen. 
A feeling that whatever happens, it’s okay. 
So you cannot be playful if you’re frightened that moving in some direction will be wrong.
Something you shouldn’t have done. 
You’re either free to play or you’re not. 
So the best way to get the confidence to do that is to know that while you’re being creative, nothing is wrong” 

#creativity #johncleese #diyprojects #artoftheday

I wish I could start every day like this. Come along as I make a latte with fresh mint from the garden and my @mrcoffee 4 in 1 latte maker. Here’s the info for making one yourself.
Ingredients:
- Fresh mint leaves
- 1 tbsp organic cane sugar
- 2 tbsp hot water
- Milk of choice
- Coffee beans 

Directions:
1. Using a pestle and mortar (or small bowl and wooden spoon), crush the mint leaves and sugar 
2. Add the hot water and mix until the liquid turns green
3. Strain the liquid mint mixture into a glass filled with ice
4. Add the coffee, then the frothed milk
5. Add a mint garnish and enjoy!

Thanks to @mrcoffee for supporting my love of good coffee. Definitely recommend checking out their latte maker if you’re looking for an upgrade!

I’ve always felt opposed to the common advice of finding one niche and sticking to it.

It’s taken me awhile to learn this, because I have so many interests and passions. And for a long time I felt the pressure that I had to focus on just one thing in order to be successful at it. 

But that ain’t true. To keep growing you’ve gotta push your creativity, you can’t get too comfortable. 

Plus it’s more fun and interesting this way! 

You should be experimenting, saying yes to all sorts of projects and opportunities that come your way. Learning from trial and error is the best. Get out of your comfort zone, push yourself and be patient

Hoping this can resonate with someone who needs to hear it. Thanks for reading all this and for the support! 
#creativity #artist #diyprojects #artoftheday
